00:51:02,376 --> 00:51:05,128
Let me in.

275
00:51:07,298 --> 00:51:09,924
Let me in.

276
00:51:13,846 --> 00:51:16,639
Let me in.

277
00:51:21,270 --> 00:51:23,980
Let me in.

278
00:51:23,981 --> 00:51:26,357
Let me in.

279
00:51:37,203 --> 00:51:38,995
Who is it?

280
00:51:44,210 --> 00:51:46,127
Who's there?

281
00:52:09,986 --> 00:52:13,154
Robert.

282
00:52:13,781 --> 00:52:15,907
Robert.

283
00:52:19,453 --> 00:52:22,997
Robert.

284
00:52:47,231 --> 00:52:49,607
Morgan.

285
00:52:49,608 --> 00:52:52,985
We're going to kill you, Morgan.

286
00:52:53,446 --> 00:52:57,156
Morgan? Do you hear?

287
00:52:57,450 --> 00:52:59,909
Morgan.

288
00:53:01,704 --> 00:53:04,455
Morgan!

289
00:53:05,499 --> 00:53:08,167
Do you hear, Morgan?

290
00:53:08,502 --> 00:53:13,589
Morgan? Do you hear, Morgan?

291
00:54:08,938 --> 00:54:12,273
If Cortman thinks he can get
to me by destroying my car...

292
00:54:12,274 --> 00:54:14,734
his wits are getting dull.

293
00:54:19,782 --> 00:54:22,200
This convertible would be nice.

294
00:54:22,201 --> 00:54:24,535
Probably handles well.

295
00:54:24,620 --> 00:54:26,996
But I can't think of comfort.

296
00:54:26,997 --> 00:54:30,249
There was a time when
I shopped for a car...

297
00:54:30,334 --> 00:54:33,044
but now I'm looking for a hearse.

298
00:54:33,087 --> 00:54:36,088
This station wagon will have to do.

299
00:55:19,592 --> 00:55:21,258
Alive.

300
00:55:21,677 --> 00:55:23,552
It's alive!

301
00:55:28,684 --> 00:55:31,560
Wait. Don't run away!

302
00:55:31,604 --> 00:55:33,438
Come back here.

303
00:55:33,439 --> 00:55:35,731
Don't run away!

304
00:55:40,529 --> 00:55:43,906
Come back. Come back here!

305
00:55:46,493 --> 00:55:48,703
Wherever he is, I've got to find him.

306
00:55:48,704 --> 00:55:51,581
If I have to search every street,
every house, every alley...

307
00:55:51,582 --> 00:55:54,834
every inch of this town,
I've got to find him.

308
00:55:59,757 --> 00:56:01,590
Come back!

309
00:56:05,554 --> 00:56:08,013
Hey, boy, where are you?

310
00:56:14,772 --> 00:56:17,440
Where are you, pal? Come here.

311
00:56:51,350 --> 00:56:53,309
They're dead.

312
00:56:53,310 --> 00:56:55,519
They've been staked!

313
00:57:04,113 --> 00:57:08,157
But these are made of
iron, not wood like mine.

314
00:57:12,329 --> 00:57:15,623
Someone else is alive in this world.

315
00:57:15,624 --> 00:57:18,876
But where are they?
Where are they hiding?

316
00:57:24,508 --> 00:57:28,260
How many are there?
Where did they come from?

317
00:57:28,387 --> 00:57:30,846
Why haven't I seen them?

318
00:57:38,397 --> 00:57:40,731
This is Robert Morgan.

319
00:57:41,358 --> 00:57:45,820
If somebody can hear me, answer me.

320
00:57:46,697 --> 00:57:49,240
For God's sake, answer me!

321
00:57:52,661 --> 00:57:54,912
This is K-O-K-W calling.

322
00:57:54,913 --> 00:57:57,122
K-O-K-W calling.

323
00:57:57,333 --> 00:57:59,124
Answer me.

324
00:58:33,285 --> 00:58:36,662
So you finally decided to come back.

325
00:58:37,289 --> 00:58:39,290
It's alright boy.

326
00:58:39,291 --> 00:58:41,250
Good boy.

327
00:58:42,127 --> 00:58:44,545
Oh, no.

328
00:58:48,008 --> 00:58:50,092
Don't worry, boy.

329
00:58:50,344 --> 00:58:53,804
You're going to be all right.
Yes, you are.

330
00:59:07,361 --> 00:59:10,571
There now, we've got
you all cleaned up.

331
00:59:11,782 --> 00:59:13,658
You're gonna feel better.

332
00:59:13,659 --> 00:59:17,578
Gonna put you down here
now and you can rest.

333
00:59:17,996 --> 00:59:20,706
Got you all cleaned up.

334
00:59:38,100 --> 00:59:40,935
You know they're out
there, don't you?

335
00:59:40,936 --> 00:59:43,938
You poor driven thing.

336
00:59:49,361 --> 00:59:52,237
Everything's going to be all right.

337
00:59:52,573 --> 00:59:55,032
Nobody's going to hurt you.

338
00:59:55,784 --> 00:59:58,619
Everything's going to be all right.

339
00:59:59,371 --> 01:00:01,205
All right.

340
01:00:01,415 --> 01:00:03,958
You're going to get better.

341
01:00:03,959 --> 01:00:06,919
We're going to have lots
of happy times together.

342
01:00:07,754 --> 01:00:11,090
You'll see. Everything's
going to be fine.

343
01:01:06,021 --> 01:01:08,313
What's the use?

344
01:02:09,585 --> 01:02:13,462
Wait, I'm not going to hurt you.
Can't you understand? Wait!

345
01:02:34,359 --> 01:02:35,943
Wait.

346
01:02:36,069 --> 01:02:39,571
I'm not going to hurt you. Wait.

347
01:02:41,199 --> 01:02:44,660
I couldn't be out here in the
daylight if I was one of them.

348
01:02:44,661 --> 01:02:48,163
You know that they can't
come out until sundown.

349
01:02:48,498 --> 01:02:52,584
Do you want to come with me,
or do you want to face them?

350
01:04:22,426 --> 01:04:25,969
- You feeling better?
- Yes.

351
01:04:26,179 --> 01:04:30,015
- Would you like a cup of coffee?
- Thank you.

352
01:04:42,821 --> 01:04:46,698
- You seem very well organized here.
- Yeah.

353
01:04:48,368 --> 01:04:50,827
My name is Ruth Collins.

354
01:04:53,498 --> 01:04:55,499
I was married.

355
01:04:57,252 --> 01:04:59,378
I lost my husband.

356
01:05:01,923 --> 01:05:03,882
You are alone?

357
01:05:06,303 --> 01:05:08,637
- You were married?
- Yes.

358
01:05:09,514 --> 01:05:11,265
Children?

359
01:05:12,559 --> 01:05:14,393
A daughter.

360
01:05:35,999 --> 01:05:38,166
What are you doing?

361
01:05:41,213 --> 01:05:43,964
Please, stop! Stop it, please!

362
01:05:43,965 --> 01:05:45,841
You're making me sick.

363
01:05:45,842 --> 01:05:49,261
Why do you turn away?
Why do you turn away?

364
01:05:56,019 --> 01:05:59,604
- You are infected.
- No.

365
01:06:02,526 --> 01:06:05,736
Infected systems are
allergic to garlic.

366
01:06:06,404 --> 01:06:09,614
- You think I'm one of them.
- You will be.

367
01:06:11,785 --> 01:06:14,787
You've made up your
mind just because I...

368
01:06:14,788 --> 01:06:17,331
You can't change the
facts by talking.

369
01:06:17,332 --> 01:06:20,167
Facts? What facts?

370
01:06:21,086 --> 01:06:22,837
That I got sick?

371
01:06:22,838 --> 01:06:25,381
I've had a sensitive
stomach all my life.

372
01:06:25,382 --> 01:06:29,760
I saw my husband killed. Torn to
pieces, right in front of our house.

373
01:06:29,761 --> 01:06:32,179
I've been wandering ever since.

374
01:06:32,180 --> 01:06:35,515
Hiding at night.
Not eating more than scraps.

375
01:06:35,559 --> 01:06:40,479
Sick with mourning,
sick with fear, unable to sleep.

376
01:06:41,565 --> 01:06:43,607
Then you shout at me.

377
01:06:43,608 --> 01:06:46,151
You chase me across
the field, hit me...

378
01:06:46,152 --> 01:06:48,779
drag me to this house,
and to top it all...

379
01:06:48,780 --> 01:06:52,658
when I get sick because you shove
a piece of reeking garlic in my face...

380
01:06:52,659 --> 01:06:55,077
you tell me I'm infected.

381
01:06:56,872 --> 01:06:58,539
- Where are you going?
- Let me go.

382
01:06:58,540 --> 01:07:00,249
You can't go out there.
It's almost sunset.

383
01:07:00,250 --> 01:07:02,084
- Let me go, I said.
- You can't go out there now.

384
01:07:02,085 --> 01:07:05,462
In a few minutes the streets
will be full of them.

385
01:07:05,463 --> 01:07:08,424
- I don't care.
- At least let me give you a blood test.

386
01:07:08,425 --> 01:07:10,384
Don't touch me.

387
01:07:11,344 --> 01:07:13,845
Don't touch me.

388
01:07:14,848 --> 01:07:17,057
Don't touch me.

389
01:07:26,359 --> 01:07:29,778
You must be hungry.
I'll fix you some dinner.

390
01:07:48,632 --> 01:07:51,967
- You know, you should eat.
- I can't.

391
01:08:07,400 --> 01:08:11,236
- You seem used to them.
- As much as anybody could be.

392
01:08:11,488 --> 01:08:15,407
I'm not frightened of them anymore,
if that's what you mean.

393
01:08:15,408 --> 01:08:19,662
I protect myself against them,
but only because there are so many.

394
01:08:19,663 --> 01:08:21,914
Individually, they're weak.

395
01:08:21,915 --> 01:08:25,459
Mentally incompetent,
like animals after a long famine.

396
01:08:25,460 --> 01:08:27,211
If they weren't...

397
01:08:27,212 --> 01:08:31,382
they surely would've found a way
of breaking in here a long time ago.

398
01:08:31,383 --> 01:08:33,592
Come out, Morgan.

399
01:08:36,388 --> 01:08:38,221
Hear that?

400
01:08:38,515 --> 01:08:40,724
That's Ben Cortman.

401
01:08:40,976 --> 01:08:43,560
- He was my friend.
- Your friend?

402
01:08:43,561 --> 01:08:45,646
He was like a kid brother.

403
01:08:45,647 --> 01:08:48,815
If I could find him
and destroy him...

404
01:08:49,484 --> 01:08:51,902
But you said he was your friend.

405
01:08:51,903 --> 01:08:56,406
When I find him I'll drive a stake
through him, just like all the others.

406
01:09:01,955 --> 01:09:06,291
But you lived through all this.
Do you know why?

407
01:09:07,335 --> 01:09:09,628
Perhaps I was chosen.

408
01:09:11,214 --> 01:09:13,215
That's a laugh.

409
01:09:15,010 --> 01:09:18,262
Or perhaps it's because a long time
ago when I worked in Panama...

410
01:09:18,263 --> 01:09:21,014
I was bitten in my sleep by a bat.

411
01:09:21,474 --> 01:09:23,475
My theory is that the...

412
01:09:23,768 --> 01:09:26,937
the bat had previously
acquired the vampire germ.

413
01:09:26,938 --> 01:09:28,731
By the time it entered my blood...

414
01:09:28,732 --> 01:09:31,483
it had been strained and
weakened by the bat's system.

415
01:09:31,484 --> 01:09:35,320
As a result, I have immunity.

416
01:09:36,322 --> 01:09:39,908
It's only a guess,
but it's all I have to go on.

417
01:09:42,996 --> 01:09:47,832
You don't think that
I'm immune, do you?

418
01:09:48,001 --> 01:09:51,378
It's a simple matter to find
out whether you are or not.

419
01:09:57,343 --> 01:10:01,930
What will you do if I am infected?

420
01:10:02,182 --> 01:10:04,099
Cure me?

421
01:10:06,269 --> 01:10:08,395
You don't have to answer.

422
01:10:08,396 --> 01:10:10,897
I know as well as you do...

423
01:10:11,983 --> 01:10:13,650
it's incurable.

424
01:10:13,651 --> 01:10:15,652
There might be a way.

425
01:10:15,653 --> 01:10:20,740
If not of killing the germ, at least of
containing it, keeping it from spreading.

426
01:10:21,242 --> 01:10:24,578
If I had the equipment, the time.

427
01:10:25,413 --> 01:10:27,497
Which you don't.

428
01:11:09,249 --> 01:11:11,208
You are one of them.

429
01:11:11,209 --> 01:11:15,378
I was. And without that
injection, I'll be one again.

430
01:11:15,797 --> 01:11:17,714
What do you mean?

431
01:11:17,715 --> 01:11:20,884
- You found a solution?
- That's right.

432
01:11:21,261 --> 01:11:23,720
Exactly as you said it could be.

433
01:11:24,389 --> 01:11:26,598
I take that for it.

434
01:11:28,768 --> 01:11:30,310
What is it?

435
01:11:30,770 --> 01:11:33,605
Defibrinated blood, plus vaccine.

436
01:11:34,399 --> 01:11:36,525
The blood feeds the germ...

437
01:11:36,526 --> 01:11:39,111
the vaccine keeps it isolated...

438
01:11:39,112 --> 01:11:41,988
and prevents it from multiplying.

439
01:11:43,825 --> 01:11:46,618
We've had it for some time now.

440
01:11:46,828 --> 01:11:48,328
We?

441
01:11:48,746 --> 01:11:49,663
We?

442
01:11:49,664 --> 01:11:52,457
There are quite a number of us.

443
01:11:53,376 --> 01:11:56,086
And I thought you were alone.

444
01:11:56,296 --> 01:11:58,755
I was going to cure you.

445
01:11:59,174 --> 01:12:01,633
- Does that amuse you?
- No.

446
01:12:03,386 --> 01:12:06,471
Now, I want the truth.

447
01:12:07,849 --> 01:12:10,475
I want all of it. Why are you here?

448
01:12:10,476 --> 01:12:13,187
To find out if you know
any more than we do.

449
01:12:13,188 --> 01:12:14,980
You know far less.

450
01:12:14,981 --> 01:12:18,775
We're alive. Infected, yes.
But alive.

451
01:12:18,943 --> 01:12:21,861
We're going to reorganize society.

452
01:12:22,197 --> 01:12:26,867
Do away with all those wretched creatures
who are neither alive nor dead.

453
01:12:26,868 --> 01:12:29,744
Start everything all over again.

454
01:12:30,914 --> 01:12:33,123
And you want me to join?

455
01:12:33,625 --> 01:12:35,792
You can't join us.

456
01:12:35,793 --> 01:12:38,128
You're a monster to them.

457
01:12:38,129 --> 01:12:40,839
Why do you think I
ran when I saw you?

458
01:12:40,840 --> 01:12:43,467
Even though I was
assigned to spy on you.

459
01:12:43,468 --> 01:12:47,012
Because I was so terrified
of what I'd heard about you.

460
01:12:47,013 --> 01:12:51,182
You're a legend in the city.
Living by day instead of night.

461
01:12:51,476 --> 01:12:55,229
Leaving, as evidence of your
existence, bloodless corpses.

462
01:12:55,230 --> 01:12:58,815
Many of the people you
destroyed were still alive.

463
01:12:59,651 --> 01:13:03,236
Many of them were loved ones
of the people in my group.

464
01:13:04,581 --> 01:13:06,165
I didn't know.

465
01:13:06,166 --> 01:13:07,771
Is there any way you
can get out of here?

466
01:13:07,772 --> 01:13:09,807
What do you mean?

467
01:13:10,308 --> 01:13:12,847
They're coming after you tonight.

468
01:13:12,848 --> 01:13:18,168
That's why I was sent here.
To prevent you from resisting them.

469
01:13:18,169 --> 01:13:24,090
I'm supposed to keep
you here until they come.

470
01:13:24,884 --> 01:13:27,969
- To kill me?
- Yes.

471
01:13:28,179 --> 01:13:31,055
Your new society sounds charming.

472
01:13:31,432 --> 01:13:35,477
The beginning of any society
is never charming or gentle.

473
01:13:35,561 --> 01:13:39,397
And you pretended to be
shocked at my violence.

474
01:13:39,941 --> 01:13:42,359
Well, what are you waiting for?

475
01:13:42,360 --> 01:13:45,904
Why don't you go on and use it?
Get it over with. Use it!

476
01:13:45,905 --> 01:13:47,864
Get it over with!

477
01:13:58,042 --> 01:14:00,293
Now you know.

478
01:14:01,838 --> 01:14:06,174
What are you going to do?

479
01:15:47,026 --> 01:15:51,195
- What are you doing?
- It's already done.

480
01:15:51,531 --> 01:15:53,031
What?

481
01:15:59,956 --> 01:16:01,915
Look.

482
01:16:02,250 --> 01:16:03,917
Look!

483
01:16:17,557 --> 01:16:20,975
You see? It worked, Ruth.

484
01:16:21,602 --> 01:16:24,687
The antibodies in my blood worked.

485
01:16:24,981 --> 01:16:27,566
My blood has saved you, Ruth.

486
01:16:27,567 --> 01:16:32,487
Do you know what this means?
You and I can save all the others.

487
01:16:32,697 --> 01:16:36,407
We won't be alone.
We'll never be alone again.

488
01:16:36,993 --> 01:16:39,369
You are sure?

489
01:16:39,954 --> 01:16:41,788
Wait.

490
01:16:58,890 --> 01:17:01,140
Don't be afraid.

491
01:17:27,535 --> 01:17:29,212
- Where are you going?
- I have to get out of here...

492
01:17:29,213 --> 01:17:31,156
- and tell them you're not a threat to us.
- You can't go out there.

493
01:17:31,157 --> 01:17:34,063
You can save all of us. When they
come here there won't be time...

494
01:17:34,064 --> 01:17:37,060
for questions and answers.
They'll come to kill.

495
01:17:37,061 --> 01:17:40,805
For God's sake, Robert, let me go.
Oh Robert, please.

496
01:17:40,806 --> 01:17:43,349
Ruth, look. Tomorrow.

497
01:17:43,809 --> 01:17:46,936
Please. Robert.

498
01:17:46,938 --> 01:17:50,606
Tomorrow, Ruth.
Tomorrow will be all right.

499
01:17:51,651 --> 01:17:53,860
Robert, no.

500
01:18:14,840 --> 01:18:16,967
- Robert.
- Yes, Ruth?

501
01:18:16,968 --> 01:18:20,553
- What if this doesn't last?
- But it will.

502
01:18:21,055 --> 01:18:24,099
I've already checked it
under the microscope.

503
01:18:24,100 --> 01:18:26,309
Wait, I'll show you.

504
01:18:26,769 --> 01:18:29,228
I'll prove it to you.
I'll check it again.

505
01:18:50,710 --> 01:18:54,420
Ruth, just take a look at this.

